  "text": "Moreover, it is required by Chickering [CITATION_1] in his definition that each local score term q D (i|B), for i ∈ N and B ⊆ N \\ {i}, only depends on the database projection D {i}∪B . This is a natural requirement from the computational point of view, implying that the score for sparse graphs can be computed from low-dimensional projections of the database. One can re-write (5) in terms of η G :",
